🚦 Future of IoT in Smart Cities
📌 Overview

This project is a case study on how IoT is shaping the future of smart cities, focusing on applications like transportation, energy, and public safety.

🎯 Objective

To study IoT applications in smart cities

To analyze future trends and challenges

To understand smart transportation systems

🌐 Key Applications

Smart traffic management

Smart energy systems

Waste management

Environmental monitoring

🚦 Practical Example: Traffic Light System
⚙️ Components

Arduino UNO

Red, Yellow, Green LEDs

Resistors

🔌 Circuit Description

Pin 13 → Red LED

Pin 12 → Yellow LED

Pin 11 → Green LED

🔄 Working

Red → Stop

Yellow → Wait

Green → Go

LEDs operate in sequence using Arduino

🌍 IoT Concept

Sensors detect traffic density

Data sent to cloud systems

Signals adjusted dynamically

📊 Outcome

This project demonstrates how IoT can improve traffic flow and reduce congestion in smart cities.

🔮 Future Scope

AI-based traffic control

Emergency vehicle priority

Smart vehicle integration

📚 Conclusion

IoT will play a major role in building smart, efficient, and sustainable cities in the future.
